From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 13:17:42 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 18/18] feat(borderfix): add vf_pelorus_borderfix_vulkan
 (dirty-line/border repair, Vulkan)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Cropped, telecined, and analog-captured sources carry garbage rows/columns at
the frame edge (half-pixels, clamp lines, head-switching noise) that cost the
encoder bits and read as a dirty border. The GPU equivalent of FFmpeg's
fillborders=smear: each pixel inside the dirty band is replaced by the nearest
clean interior pixel, smearing the good edge outward. Runs in VRAM so the
Pelorus pipeline never has to drop to a CPU fillborders + the hwdownload round
trip it would cost. Bit-depth-agnostic (FF_VK_REP_FLOAT UNORM); all planes by
default. Band widths are per-plane pixels.

Pure pixel transform — does NOT link libpelorus (deps-only registration). The
reference shader libpelorus/shaders/pelorus_borderfix.comp and the inline GLSL
are kept in lockstep. AVOptions: left/right/top/bottom (band widths), planes.

ADR: docs/adr/0128-borderfix.md
